SIMPLE: cropper
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cropper
<hw>Crop"per</hw> <pr>(kr?p"p?r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>One that crops.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A variety of pigeon with a large crop; a
pouter.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Mech.)</fld> <def>A machine for cropping, as for
shearing off bolts or rod iron, or for facing cloth.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>A fall on one's head when riding at full speed, as
in hunting; hence, a sudden failure or collapse.</def>
<mark>[Slang.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cropsick</ent>⟦br⟧
